 his left hand, his witcher''s sword, the woman he loves, the daughter he had gained by a miracle, his faith... Well, I thought, he must have been left with something. But I was wrong. He has nothing now. Not even a razor."Dandelion remained silent. The dryad did not move."I asked if you had a hand in this," she began a moment later. "But I think there was no need. It''s obvious you had a hand in it. It''s obvious you are his friend. And if someone has friends, and he loses everything in spite of that, it''s obvious the friends are to blame. For what they did, or for what they didn''t do.', 1292, 0), (189386, 'And if someone has friends, and he loses everything in spite of that, it''s obvious the friends are to blame. For what they did, or for what they didn''t do.', 1292, 0), (189387, '...in addition to feeling sick and tired and feverish and nauseated, I also felt forgotten. And there was no easy cure for that.', 31488, 0), (189388, 'Friends are only friends when the fights don''t matter because you understand each other better in the end.', 34582, 0), (189389, 'When life gives up on you, know that your best friend will always be there.', 25833, 0), (189390, 'Never make enemies of anyone younger or healthier than you are. They write your history.', 8257, 0), (189391, 'Usually after a good puke you feel better right away. We hugged each other and then said good-bye and went off to opposite ends of the hall to lie down in our own rooms. There is nothing like puking with somebody to make you into old friends.', 140, 0), (189392, 'And you came to Finland to build a station?""No I came here on vacation to visit a friend.""That''s good," the driver said. "Vacations and friends are the two best things in life.', 48, 0), (189393, 'A woman will endure many wounds in her lifetime, but the betrayal of a friend is one of the most difficult to overcome.', 18655, 0), (189394, 'One day we both are going to realize that our Friendship was worth the fight.', 33069, 0), (189395, 'Who who whose smell in the air of her room, whose fingerprints all over her friends’ secret places.', 546, 0), (189396, 'He asked me IF I MISSED YOU. I didn''t answer and walked away keeping my eyes closed. And then shedding a tear whisper: So much', 33069, 0), (189397, 'I''m friends with a guy who is friends with a former Playboy model. So I guess you could say I''m 1 degree away from 212 degrees.', 10209, 0), (189398, 'I find great happiness in my relationships with old friends, living mirrors that reflect histories of laughter and sorrow, triumphs and failures, births and deaths, on both sides.', 1088, 0), (189399, 'No true friendship takes account of credit and debt. It gives freely, without thought of compensation or reward.', 27554, 0), (189400, 'My squad was my family, my gun was my provider and protector, and my rule was to kill or be killed. The extent of my thoughts didn’t go much beyond that. We had been fighting for over two years, and killing had become a daily activity. I felt no pity for anyone.', 7857, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (189401, 'There is nothing more valuable in the writing process than a friend to hold you accountable to your own potential.', 29732, 0), (189402, 'I just could not leave the people who ever fill my heart. But if people leave, well, like today myself. That''s why I''m afraid to get acquainted with a lot of people because I''m afraid of losing a lot of people too. In reality I always get acquainted with many people, how is this?', 34583, 0), (189403, 'Doing comedy for a living is, in a lot of ways, like a pony and a camel trying to escape from the zoo. It’s a ridiculous endeavor and has a low probability of success, but most importantly, it is way easier if you’re with a friend.', 1498, 0), (189404, 'Sometimes your dearest friend whom you reveal most of your secrets to becomes so deadly and unfriendly without knowing that they were not really your friend.', 332, 0), (189405, 'Violence was a disease Gansey didn''t think he could catch. But all around him, his friends were slowly infected.', 184, 0), (189406, 'A year of ending and beginning, a year of loss and finding...and all of you were with me through the storm. I drink your health, your wealth, your fortune for long years to come, and I hope for many more days in which we can gather like this.', 9987, 0), (189407, 'It is not until you rhyme with a person that makes you their perfect match, it is when you are satisfied with each others peculiarities, and find jewels in their loopholes.', 332, 0), (189408, 'I should rip your eyes out,” Newt said, spraying Thomas with spit. “Teach you a lesson in stupidity.Why’d you come over here? You expected a bloody hug? Huh? A nice sit-down to talk about the goodtimes in the Glade?', 1493, 0), (189409, 'If you need true friend ''a cup of tea can be'' it gives you company, listen without complain and makes you fresh anytime,anywhere', 32026, 0), (189410, 'It''s disappointing enough to know that the people we love will sometimes lie, but it is almost worse when we remember that strangers do this too, and this is why it is best not to admit our lies to strangers because it is not pleasant to learn that someone will lie even when there is little to nothing at stake.', 4534, 0), (189411, 'He was like a book, where each chapter picks up pace until you can''t put it down. That''s when you know you''ve made a friend - when you want to read more of his story.', 412, 0), (189412, 'Satisfaction is not the achievement of what we want, but the awareness of what we have.', 5034, 0), (189413, 'Friends are like books, you learn from every one of them.', 2586, 0), (189414, 'Friends are the best anti-depressants; with only positive effects, no side-effects.', 34584, 0), (189415, 'If you want to make peace, you don’t talk to your friends. You talk to your enemies.', 34585, 0), (189416, 'Happiness held is the beginning', 34586, 0), (189417, 'why shine as bright as the sun, when you can shine as bright as the moon and let the stars shine beside you', 34587, 0), (189418, 'They weren''t making much sense; she decided they were having an argument as old and comfortable as an armchair, the kind of argument that no one ever really wins or loses, but which can go on for ever, if both parties are willing.', 14, 0), (189419, 'You can always make enemies of your friends,'' said Sumael. ''Making friends of your enemies is harder labor.', 1466, 0), (189420, 'Some of our friends put our enemies out of work.', 34588, 0), (189421, 'The true friend . . . knows that you need him in that very moment –not tomorrow, not next week. By next week you may happy, or you may be dead.', 34589, 0), (189422, 'You''ll know I love you when you''re not making out with my friends.', 32323, 0), (189423, 'God Made Nature, Nature Need Friends.', 26084, 0), (189424, 'Nurture the qualities in yourself that you desire in your friends.', 4404, 0), (189425, 'You can pick your friends, and you can pick your nose, but you can''t pick your friends nose.', 9, 0), (189426, 'Fire false friends. They are in to fast-forward your fall and failure.', 3301, 0), (189427, 'They were the best sort of friends. The sort everyone hopes for but no one deserves, least of all me.', 313, 0), (189428, 'Remember as there are people that can help you to roll the boat of your dreams, there are also people who can drill holes under that boat to make it sink.', 3301, 0), (189429, 'Every person you meet has been assigned to play a role in your story as you are assigned to play one in someone else’s. I often say that the people we come across can be one of the four kinds. They can be like pebbles, fountains, quagmire or bridges. Pebbles are those who you meet commonly and in abundance. They do not facilitate anything great but they help you continue walking on this journey of life. Everyone you cross in life without really connecting with them are pebbles. Then there are fountains – who spring water of happiness on you. They bring positivity and joy; they nourish your soul and irrigate the seeds of good thoughts. Your friends, well-wishers are all fountains. Then, on the other end of the spectrum, you have quagmires. These are the people who cause you pain. Now, even some pebbles may have caused you pain as it happens if you tread on a barbed pebble but the difference is that quagmires do that on purpose. They pull you down, induce fear and negativity by discouraging you and worrying you. They will not let you move on – that’s why they keep you bogged down in your failures. Finally, the rarest ones are the bridges – they connect you to unchartered ground that you wouldn’t have reached on your own. They unite you to your destiny. With them, your plane of consciousness expands, you see things you have not seen before; your life becomes more aware, more enlightened. Your parents, your teachers and anyone who touches your life and transcends it into something more beautiful – they are all bridges.', 34590, 0), (189430, 'Reading a book 